1. Create directory {your_joomla_site}/libraries/dao
	and put there:
	- autoload.class.php 
	- entity.class.php

2. Create {your_joomla_site}/libraries/dao/entities
	and put all entities (dao objects) there


3. To use it, you need to update following files (Joomla! version: 1.5.16):
libraries/joomla/database/database.php
753: - function loadObjectList( $key='' )
753: + function loadObjectList( $key='', $class = 'stdClass' )

libraries/joomla/database/database/mysql.php
456: - function loadObjectList( $key='' )
456: + function loadObjectList( $key='', $class = 'stdClass' )
462: - while ($row = mysql_fetch_object( $cur )) {
462: + while ($row = mysql_fetch_object( $cur, $class )) {

libraries/joomla/database/database/mysqli.php
472: - function loadObjectList( $key='' )
472: + function loadObjectList( $key='', $class = 'stdClass' )
478: - while ($row = mysqli_fetch_object( $cur )) {
478: + while ($row = mysqli_fetch_object( $cur, $class )) {

4. In every controller you want to use DAO add line:
include_once( JPATH_BASE .'/libraries/dao/autoload.php' );

Have a fun!
